------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Assignment 4: File Hiding 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Credits
    Nicolas Appel
    Wenwen Chen
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Description
    - Hide files with the prefix “rootkit_” from the user when listing directories 
      (ls).
    - The hidden file is still accessible to anyone who knows that it is there.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation instructions
    - Compile the module
      # make
    - Clean project
      # make clean
    - View the information of rootkit.ko
      # modinfo rootkit.ko
    - Load rootkit.ko
      # insmod rootkit.ko
    - View currently loaded kernel modules in the system
      # lsmod
    - Unload rookit.ko
      # rmmod rootkit
    - Test (Files with the prefix "rootkit_" should not be listed any more, but are 
      still accessible)
      $ ls (-a -l)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Implementation Details
    - All code related to file hiding can be found in the file_hiding.* files
    - Using the tool strace, one can find out that "ls" uses the system call 
      "sys_getdents" with file descriptor 3
    - Hooking the system call "sys_getdents":
      - When fd is 3, the struct linux_dirent will be iterated and checked for 
        occurrence of dirent->d_name (file name) starting with the predefined  
        prefix "rootkit_"
      - Files beginning with the predefined prefix will be removed from the list 
        by shifting the rest of the list accordingly using the function "memmove"
    Unhooking:
    - Restore original "sys_getdents"
    - The function "unhide file" prevents errors by blocking module removal 
      until every my_sys_getdents has finished. It does so by checking the 
      reference counter r_count and printing '\n' until all blocking my_sys_getdents 
      calls return.
